value.0: Yeah? Ya want something, I bet?
Tsk. Tsk. If you don't die some wretched death, m'<lord/lady>, come back sometime and we'll make a deal, aye?
Me? Why, I'm none other than the renowned rogue, Tomi Undergallows! Grin to my friends, Tomi Grin to the lasses, and that damned halfling to anyone in a position of respectable authority.
I can forgive you for not having heard of me, however. I hail most recently from Calimport... and that's a long way for even my reputation to travel. I give it another week, personally.

So let's negotiate a bit, shall we? I can place my superior skills of theft, lockpicking and swordplay at your disposal for any task you choose. I think, ummm, some of the treasures and gold ya find will be sufficient.
Well, fine. Tomi Undergallows has better things to do. I'm sure someone there's a better party somewhere anyways.
Oi, it looks like you already have a henchman! There won't be enough loot for all of us ya hear?
Easily done. Come back when it's just you and me, eh?
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Fat chance. No way I'm sharing with another henchman! Come back when it's just you and me, eh?
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Okay okay, you've talked me into it! Let's get going then, shall we?
Good, good! I smell adventure at hand! Or I need to wash my socks, one of the two...
Hey now! Something else ya need?
Eh? What can Tomi do for ya?
Fair enough. Back to the adventure!
Wha-aat? Are you kidding me? You want to break up a great team?
Let's get back to it then!
Alrighty. I think I can find my own way back. You can find me in the Trade o' Blades if ya needs me again.
Okey-dokey.

value.0: Aye? Don't suppose there's some reason for us ta chat, is there? Naw, didn't bloody well think so.
Yer ugly and you smell like a rotten skunk!
Not really. Goodbye.
I might. Who are you?
I'll be going now.
I could use a good rogue. Welcome aboard, Tomi.
Fine. Forget I asked.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Trust me, where we are going, there will be riches for us all.
Never mind.
I think we need to part ways.
No, never mind.
Yes. Go.
Never mind.
